name: R ANGE R ANGE R ANGE R
description: Does this say RANGE RANGER ANGER? Or RANGER ANGER ANGER? As stated on a previous page, negative space is so important to context. Where are the silent notes in my jazz score of art? Who decides where the spaces between the R and the A go? It's you, the reader. You decide on what you're reading. Think of this as something akin to those "choose-your-own-adventure books" from the 80s. I can't resist a good Willy Wonka quote, "We are the music makers, and we are the dreamers of dreams." Just because I made the work doesn't necessarily mean you have to take my narrative. You can create your own. In fact, I love when people tell me they see a completely different story or thought in what I write. It gives diversity of thought and input; a true conversation.
